# Phase 35.4 · Docs, Runbooks, and API Examples

Repository: `cvsz/zdash`

Execution profile: DeepSeek V4 Flash Free / fast free coding model.

Goal:
Finalize zDash documentation for release readiness without changing source code unless a docs command exposes a critical broken reference.

This pass is docs-first. Do not edit backend/frontend source files.

---

## Safety invariants

- Do not commit `.env`, secrets, tokens, private keys, generated logs, GPG passphrases, or local Codex run artifacts.
- `docs/prompts/codex-runs/` remains local-only and untracked.
- API examples must use backend port `8005` only.
- Do not introduce `localhost:8000` or `BACKEND_PORT=8000`.
- Trading and AI Trader docs must say simulation-only / not financial advice / no live execution.
- Billing docs must say mock provider is default and Stripe is disabled by default.
- Marketplace docs must say plugin sandbox/review is required by default.
- Enterprise docs must say export with secrets requires explicit typed confirmation and secrets are excluded by default.
- Cloudflare operator handoff must reference `cvsz/zeaz-platform`.

---

## Inspect first

Inspect docs and release files:

```text
README.md
docs/
docs/architecture/
docs/runbooks/
docs/prompts/
docs/AI_TRADER_CONTROL_PLANE.md
.codex/cloud/README.md
.codex/cloud/phase-runner.md
.env.example
frontend/.env.example
Makefile
```

Create an inspection summary:

```text
- docs present
- stale docs
- missing API examples
- port 8000 references
- missing safety notes
- missing validation notes
- missing troubleshooting notes
```

---

## Required README updates

Ensure README includes or links to:

- Phase 35 final release status.
- Local development quickstart.
- Backend API port `8005`.
- Frontend port `5173`.
- Validation commands.
- `make safety-scan`.
- `make validate-fast`.
- `make validate`.
- AI Trader simulation-only control plane.
- Billing model and mock provider default.
- Marketplace plugin safety model.
- Enterprise packaging and export/import safety.
- Cloudflare operator handoff to `cvsz/zeaz-platform`.
- Known non-blocking warnings.

Avoid turning README into a huge duplicated manual. Link to architecture docs/runbooks where possible.

