---

## API examples

All examples must use port `8005`:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8005/health
curl http://localhost:8005/api/ai-trader/status -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
curl http://localhost:8005/api/ai-trader/strategies -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
curl -X POST http://localhost:8005/api/ai-trader/signal \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"symbol":"XAUUSD","timeframe":"M5","strategy_id":"trend_momentum_v1","candles":[],"min_confidence":0.55}'
curl http://localhost:8005/api/billing/plans -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
curl http://localhost:8005/api/marketplace/plugins -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
curl http://localhost:8005/api/enterprise/status -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
```

Do not add examples with real tokens, real card data, real secrets, or live order execution.

---

## Troubleshooting notes

Document these as non-blocking when summaries pass:

```text
passlib crypt deprecation warning from dependency
React act(...) warnings in existing hook tests
React Router future flag warnings
intentional ErrorBoundary test Error: fail
```

Document these as blocking:

```text
backend ruff failure
pytest failed tests
frontend failed tests
npm build failure
make safety-scan failure
tracked .env or local-only prompt artifacts
old backend port 8000 in tracked runtime/source files
secret-like values in tracked runtime/source files
```

---

## Validation

Docs-only safety validation:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
make safety-scan
```

Optional fast validation:

```bash
cd ~/zdash
APP_ENV=development \
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./zdash_test.db \
PRODUCTION_SAFETY_LOCK=true \
DRY_RUN=true \
LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false \
make validate-fast
```

---

## Allowed changes

Allowed:

- README updates
- docs additions
- runbook improvements
- prompt index updates
- API examples
- troubleshooting notes
- cross-links

Not allowed:

- backend code edits
- frontend code edits
- dependency changes
- committing secrets
- adding live trading docs
- adding external broker docs as active functionality

